The primary purpose of Unit 1 Crude is to separate raw crude oil into fractions or cuts of varying hydrocarbon components. Crude oil entering the refinery is distilled in the Crude Tower. The crude is separated into fractions or products with different boiling ranges.  These are then sent to other processing areas where each stream is processed again. This unit includes the straight run gas plant.

