The purpose of Unit 18 Reformer is to convert naphtha from the Crude unit into "reformate" using a series of reactors filled with a platinum-based catalyst. "Reformate" is used as a blending component to raise the octane level in gasoline. The unit also produces an excess of hydrogen gas, which is utilized in other refinery units and the fuel gas system.

